edu.rit.util

Class LongList

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.LongList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class LongList
extends Object
implements Streamable
    Class LongList provides a list of long integers (type long) stored in a dynamically-sized array.

    Operations take constant time unless otherwise specified. n is the number of items stored in the list.

      • position

        public int position(long i)
        Get the position of the given item in this list. This involves a linear scan of the list items starting from the beginning of the list; the position of the first item encountered that is equal to the given item is returned; if there is no such item, −1 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        i - Item.
        Returns:
        Position of i in the range 0 .. size()−1, or −1 if none.

      • position

        public int position(LongPredicate predicate)
        Get the position of the first item in this list for which the given predicate is true. This involves a linear scan of the list items starting from the beginning of the list; the returned value is the position of the first item encountered for which the predicate's test() method returns true; if there is no such item, −1 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.
        Returns:
        Position of matching item in the range 0 .. size()−1, or −1 if none.

      • removeLast

        public long removeLast()

        Returns:
        Removed item, or 0 if this list is empty.

      • removeFirst

        public long removeFirst()
        Remove the item at the beginning of this list. Items at position 1 and beyond are moved backward one position. The removed item is returned. This list's size decreases by 1. If this list is empty, nothing happens and 0 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Returns:
        Removed item, or 0 if this list is empty.

      • remove

        public long remove(int p)
        Remove the item at the given position in this list. Items at position p+1 and beyond are moved backward one position. The removed item is returned. This list's size decreases by 1. If this list is empty, nothing happens and 0 is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        p - Position, in the range 0 .. size()−1.
        Returns:
        Removed item, or 0 if this list is empty.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if this list is not empty and p is out of bounds.

      • swapRemoveLast

        public long swapRemoveLast(int p)
        Swap the item at the given position with the item at the end of this list, then remove the item at the end of this list. The removed item, which used to be at the given position, is returned. This list's size decreases by 1.
        Parameters:
        p - Position, in the range 0 .. size()−1.
        Returns:
        Removed item.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if p is out of bounds.

      • forEachItemDo

        public void forEachItemDo(LongAction action)
        Perform the given action on each item in this list. For each item in this list, the given action's run() method is called, passing in the item.

        Warning: If the action adds items to or removes items from the list, the forEachItemDo() method's behavior is not specified.

        Parameters:
        action - Action.

      • forEachItemDo

        public <R> R forEachItemDo(LongActionResult<R> action)
        Perform the given action on each item in this list and return a result. For each item in this list, the given action's run() method is called, passing in the item. After all the list items have been processed, the given action's result() method is called, and its result is returned.

        Warning: If the action adds items to or removes items from the list, the forEachItemDo() method's behavior is not specified.

        Type Parameters:
        R - Result data type.
        Parameters:
        action - Action.
        Returns:
        Result of processing all the list items.

      • removeEachItemIf

        public void removeEachItemIf(LongPredicate predicate)
        Evaluate the given predicate on, and possibly remove, each item in this list. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given predicate's test() method is called, passing in the item. If the test() method returns true, the item is removed from this list. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the predicate adds items to or removes items from the list, other than by returning true, the removeEachItemIf() method's behavior is not specified.

        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.

      • toArray

        public long[] toArray(long[] array)
        Store this list's items in the given array. The first item is stored at index 0, the second item at index 1, and so on. The number of array elements set is array.length. If this list contains fewer than array.length items, the remaining array elements are set to 0.
        Parameters:
        array - Array in which to store items.
        Returns:
        The given array is returned.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if array is null.

      • toArray

        public long[] toArray(long[] array,
             int off,
             int len)
        Store this list's items in the given array. The first item is stored at index off, the second item at index off+1, and so on. The number of array elements set is len. If this list contains fewer than len items, the remaining array elements are set to 0.
        Parameters:
        array - Array in which to store items.
        off - Index at which to store first item.
        len - Number of items to store.
        Returns:
        The given array is returned.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if array is null.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if off < 0, len < 0, or off+len > array.length.
